\end_layout

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In practice, Model 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "mod:clust-dist-model"

\end_inset

 is captured in two separate model classes.
 The first is the spatially autoregressive, cross-sectional model:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$$y_i = Wy_{i_-}
\backslash
Gamma + Z
\backslash
beta +
\backslash
epsilon$$
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The second is a conventional temporally autoregressive model; it is generally
 known as an AR(1) model:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$$y_{i,t} = y_{i,t-1}
\backslash
Gamma + Z_{i,t}
\backslash
beta +
\backslash
epsilon_{i,t}$$
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This split is largely due to the relative lack of spatial panel estimators
 at the time of analysis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Variable Properties
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
