\end_layout

\end_inset

 norms (a.k.a.
 Euclidean distance), the dimensionality of the space in which these distances
 are calculated varies in number and concept.
 For example, the full expenditure portfolio set has 16 dimensions, one
 for each expenditure concept.
 In the PCA set, there are three dimensions, and each is a linear combination
 of some subset of the original 16.
\end_layout

