\begin_layout Standard
Despite the problems with pooled analysis, OLS is often a useful starting
 point for building a narrative.
 In Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Pooled-OLS-Results"

\end_inset

, it can be seen that the Gallagher Ratio (
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$prop
\backslash
_ratio$
\end_layout

\end_inset

) is really the only consistent driver of increases in cluster distance
 across models.
 The sign of the COTEL intensity (
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$intensity
\backslash
_stock$
\end_layout

\end_inset

) estimates suggest that it is also associated with larger cluster distances,
 although not with the same magnitude or precision as the Gallagher Ratio.
 These results, even if only weakly supported in the COTEL intensity case,
 suggest that COTELs are associated with forcing counties to make different
 decisions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float table
wide false
